Package: blblm
Type: Package
Title: A Bag of Little Bootstrap Package
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Alanna Gerton
Maintainer: The package maintainer <amgerton@ucdavis.edu>
Description: Use the bag of little bootstraps algorithm to compute the linear regression and logistic regression model.The user is also given the use parallel programming for each of these main functions. If the user wishes to use parallelization, then the user must specifiy `parallel = TRUE` in the arguments, otherwise it will use the default `parallel = FALSE`. The user must specify number of CPUs before using parallel programming. Please run `plan(multisession, worker = cl)` where cl is the number of CPUs before using the function with parallelization. 
